The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | ICC to take final call on Sunday
                                                                                                                                                                                                     ICC to take final call on Sunday
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The International Cricket Council (ICC) executive board will hold a teleconference on Sunday to decide the fate of the Champions Trophy, amid concerns by players about travelling to Pakistan for the event.         
	According to an ICC release, an ICC task force set up to allay the safety concerns of the Australia, New Zealand, England and South Africa boards will hold their own teleconference first, on Friday.         
	It was learnt that on Wednesday, senior ICC officials  ICC president David Morgan, chief executive Haroon Lorgat and vice-president Sharad Pawar  reviewed feedback received by the task force from Australia, New Zealand and England officials before calling for the teleconferences.         
	Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) chief executive Shafqat Naghmi was also present.         
	Sources said the Pakistani representative supported by the BCCI had taken strong exception to the continued insistence and questioning of the security arrangements .                                                                                                                                  
